dict.string: This constraint translates the autoresizing mask of a view to Auto Layout.
This constraint represents the intrinsic content size of the view.
This constraint has been automatically generated by Interface Builder to prevent layout ambiguity.
This constraint positions a system-provided layout guide in a view controller's view.
This constraint anchors the window's position and size.
This constraint applies the system spacing between two items.
This constraint applies the system-defined width of the view because it hosts a layout engine.
This constraint applies the system-defined height of the view because it hosts a layout engine.
This constraint applies the system-defined vertical position of the view because it hosts a layout engine.
This constraint applies the system-defined horizontal position of the view because it hosts a layout engine.
This constraint applies the top inset to a safe area layout guide.
This constraint applies the bottom inset to a safe area layout guide.
This constraint applies the left inset to a safe area layout guide.
This constraint applies the right inset to a safe area layout guide.
This constraint applies the top inset to a layout margins guide.
This constraint applies the bottom inset to a layout margins guide.
This constraint applies the left inset to a layout margins guide.
This constraint applies the right inset to a layout margins guide.
This constraint defines the preferred width of a readable content guide.
This constraint horizontally centers a readable content guide within its view's layout margins.
This constraint pins the top edge of a readable content guide to its view's layout margin.
This constraint pins the bottom edge of a readable content guide to its view's layout margin.
This constraint limits the leading edge of a readable content guide to its view's layout margin.
This constraint limits the trailing edge of a readable content guide to its view's layout margin.
This constraint applies the top inset to a scroll view's layout margins guide.
This constraint applies the bottom inset to a scroll view's layout margins guide.
This constraint applies the left inset to a scroll view's layout margins guide.
This constraint applies the right inset to a scroll view's layout margins guide.
This constraint defines the horizontal position of a scroll view's content layout guide.
This constraint defines the vertical position of a scroll view's content layout guide.
This constraint defines the horizontal position of a scroll view's frame layout guide.
This constraint defines the vertical position of a scroll view's frame layout guide.
This constraint defines the width of a scroll view's frame layout guide.
This constraint defines the height of a scroll view's frame layout guide.
This constraint defines the horizontal position of a scroll view's content offset layout guide.
This constraint defines the vertical position of a scroll view's content offset layout guide.
This low-priority constraint prevents layout ambiguity of a view arranged in a stack view by minimizing its size.
This constraint aligns two views arranged in a stack view.
This constraint limits an arranged view within the stack view's bounds.
This constraint minimizes the size of a stack view's internal layout guide.
This constraint connects an arranged view or an internal layout guide to the stack view.
This low-priority constraint minimizes the size of the stack view.
This constraint applies spacing between the views arranged in a stack view.
This constraint positions a hidden view arranged in a stack view.
This constraint participates in space distribution in a stack view.
This constraint applies proportional fill distribution to the arranged subviews of a stack view.
This constraint applies equal fill distribution to the arranged subviews of a stack view.
This constraint attempts collapsing a hidden view arranged in a stack view.

This constraint prevents width ambiguity of a multiline label or text view arranged in a stack view. Priority of this constraint is derived from arranged view's hugging and compression resistance priorities.
